cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper is about improving the fidelity of neural data-to-text generation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new framework that utilizes pre-executed symbolic operations, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves designing a gating mechanism and a quantization module, which are related to deep learning and neural networks, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves experiments and evaluations, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SD (Software Engineering).
